feat: map overhaul phase 3 - multi-select, undo/redo, snap/guides, link arrows (1.33.0)

Polish pass on the map editor:
- Multi-select via shift-click or marquee drag; move/delete/align (6 edges) and
  distribute (h/v) the whole selection at once. Resize handles show only when a
  single node/shape is selected.
- Undo/redo (Ctrl+Z / Ctrl+Shift+Z / Ctrl+Y + toolbar buttons) over a snapshot
  history; copy/paste (Ctrl+C / Ctrl+V) of shapes and text labels.
- Snap-to-grid toggle (10px) with a faint grid, plus live alignment guides that
  snap a dragged node to its neighbours' edges/centers and draw blue guide lines.
- Connections gained a directional arrowhead and adjustable thickness, set per
  connection in the properties panel.

Backend/shared (separate task): map_connections.arrow/width columns + layout PUT
persistence; mapTypes.MapConnection += arrow/width; SVGMapView.ConnectionLine
renders the arrowhead + width on the map view and public share. Editor mirrors the
same render. All additive/idempotent; existing maps unaffected.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
